  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Serbia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased Responsibility in Ecology and Human Rights Teaching. The main idea of the project is to restructure and upgrade the existing courses and to develop them further according to the kindergarten and primary school curricula in Serbia. There are several groups of direct beneficiaries of the Project: teacher educators (teaching staff of the Faculty of Education in Jagodina), student-teachers (of pre-school and class teaching sections at the Faculty) and primary teachers all over Serbia. The main goal of the Project is redesigning Faculty curricula so that they support acquiring attitudes, behaviour and system of values with long-term results. The monitoring will be performed by using questionnaires for student-teachers/class teachers/English language teachers in each activity and stage of the Project. Reports will be used for comparison and final evaluation of the Project.</narrative>
  </description>
